#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
Actual Ahmed Body CFD Diagnostic Generator
Author: Chris B. Harding workflow adaptation

This script creates an actual 25-degree Ahmed body geometry and runs an
Android-safe reduced-order voxel CFD diagnostic. It is not a full finite-volume
Navier--Stokes solver; it is a validated-geometry diagnostic that exports:
  - AhmedBody_25deg_actual.obj
  - coefficient/residual history
  - 3D geometry plot
  - X-Z velocity / pressure coefficient / wake plots
  - X-Y wake top view
  - first-layer y+ maps
  - NPZ voxel field data
  - text summary
  - explicit Ahmed-body drag/lift force and coefficient calculations

The geometry is built from standard Ahmed-body values commonly used in CFD:
  length  = 1.044 m
  width   = 0.389 m
  height  = 0.288 m
  clearance = 0.050 m
  upper rear slant angle = 25 degrees
  slant length = 0.222 m

Default U_inf = 40 m/s, giving Re_L ≈ 2.8e6 in air.
"""

